Use 'unsigned int' instead of unofficial alias 'uint'

glibc headers have 'uint' typedef'd to 'unsigned int', but this isn't
guaranteed to be avaialble. Change to 'unsigned int' which is equivalent
to fix building on musl.

GUI: Rename and modify the backend python so it can be used outside GC

Make some steps in the direction of providing a Python API
for libscanmem, by improving and generalizing the class that
communicates with libscanmem.

Much more could be done, but this is enough for the needs
of the PINCE project that inspired it.

Still supports py2&3.

GC: Fix export of found addresses

The export was broken when the LockFlag mechanism was removed,
but the output format wasn't changed.
Now the format is completely incompatible with the 0.17 one,
but it's internal consistent in 0.18.

Fixes: 461b583
Closes: #361

Introduce no ptrace option and write support for /proc/mem

This option permits to avoid the usage of ptrace and
to use /proc/pid/mem to read/write to memory instead for newer kernels.

Since linux kernel 3.2.2 it is now possible to read/write to memory without ptrace,
which is useful for debugging with ptrace with another process,
at the same time we use scanmem on the targeted process.

Related: #325 #371

handlers: fix bugs in help command

First bug fixed is not allowing the user to supply more than one
argument. The second bug fixed is rearranging the code to report
errors before opening up the pager. Without this, the pager would
open with no output.

maps: Replace alloca() with variable length array

When calling alloca() for the file name in the getline() loop, then
this allocates more and more memory on the stack for all file names
within the same maps file. It has no clue about the scope/block for
which it should keep the memory. It keeps it for the whole
sm_readmaps() function. With too many memory regions, this crashes.

So replace this with a variable length array as this one respects
the scope/block it is running in, restores the stack pointer at the
start of each loop cycle and only keeps one file name on the stack
at once this way.

Suggested-by: Andrea Stacchiotti (@12345ieee)
Reported-by: CJ Kucera (@apocalyptech)
Fixes #368

show_message: check for terminal connection before getting pager

When scanmem is connected to a pipe or redirected to a file, stdout
is no longer associated with the terminal. This causes unnecessary
warning messages to appear. Add checks to avoid this.

handlers.c:
* Minor logic changes to pager code in handler__list().

commit.message:
GameConqueror.py: Fix regex used to parse list output

Fixes: #358

GameConqueror.py: Properly parse `list` output even for strings with commas

Move to a regex-based approach.

gui/GameConqueror.py: Remove the LockFlag column and mechanism

The LockFlag (allow only increase/decrease, in addition to just locking)
mechanism was never implemented, and as we got no requests for it
it makes no sense to keep a useless column around.

Also fixes an unreachable code issue found by Coverity Scan.

gui/GameConqueror.py: Remove null-check on variable we know is not null

Even when the hexview isn't started at a specific address, we use
the region start address for that role, so that we always have an address
to start the cursror on.

Found by Coverity Scan.
.travis.yml: Add gui directory to Coverity Scan via Travis

.travis.yml: Drop docker build and build on Bionic

The Docker build was just a workaround for gcc-7. Now Travis-CI
provides an Ubuntu Bionic VM image. We do not need the further layer
of complexity any more. So drop the Docker build and build on Bionic.

Fixes #350
